## Special Cases

### Package-Specific Docs
- Package READMEs: `packages/[package]/README.md` ✅
- Package docs: `docs/[package-name]/` ✅
- Don't put package docs in root ❌

### Temporary Docs
- Even temporary docs should go in `docs/temp/` or `docs/`
- Never create temporary docs in root
- Clean up temporary docs regularly

### Generated Docs
- API docs: `docs/api/` ✅
- Coverage reports: `docs/testing/` ✅
- Build artifacts: Not in repo (use CI artifacts)

## Documentation Quality

### All Docs Should:
- Be properly categorized
- Have clear, descriptive names
- Be in the correct location
- Be linked from appropriate index files
- Follow markdown best practices

### Documentation Index
- Consider creating `docs/README.md` as an index
- Link to all major documentation sections
- Keep index updated when docs are added/moved

## Cleanup Process

### Quarterly Review:
1. Scan root directory for misplaced docs
2. Move to appropriate `docs/` subdirectory
3. Update all references
4. Commit changes
5. Update CHANGELOG

### Before Major Releases:
1. Audit documentation structure
2. Move any misplaced files
3. Update documentation index
4. Verify all links work
